OL,3,CMigrants risk it all as US political
OL,4,Cdivide on Texas-Mexico border widens
OL,6,FRepublicans in Texas - mostly vocally
OL,7,Fthe state's governor Gregg Abbott -
OL,8,Fclaim that policy changes implemented
OL,9,Fby Biden, have made it much harder to
OL,10,Fexpel those crossing without a visa.
OL,12,FThe so-called Title 42 powers were
OL,13,Fended, which allowed the US
OL,14,Fauthorities to turn around migrants
OL,15,Fduring the pandemic, because of the
OL,16,Fpresence of a communicable disease.
OL,18,FSo too were Migrant Protection
OL,19,FProtocols, which forced those seeking
OL,20,Fasylum to stay in Mexico.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G7/14
