OL,6,FThe razor wire they had to scramble
OL,7,Fover after wading through the Rio
OL,8,FGrande had also left its marks.
OL,10,FI got a rare perspective on those
OL,11,Fdefences during a canoe trip down the
OL,12,Friver with local guide Jesse Fuentes.
OL,14,FHe told me he had witnessed horrendous
OL,15,Fscenes on the river, including one
OL,16,Fhaunting moment when a mother and baby
OL,17,Fwere drowning as they tried to reach
OL,18,FAmerica.
OL,20,FHe had frequently seen the bodies of
OL,21,Fthose who hadn't made it.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G12/14
