OL,6,FMost asylum seekers battle to reach
OL,7,Ftheir promised land only a hundred
OL,8,Fyards away, but for too many this
OL,9,Fswirling river was a final obstacle
OL,10,Fthey couldn't overcome.
OL,12,FWe saw migrants who had swum the
OL,13,Fwaters stranded in no man's land
OL,14,Fbeneath rows of razor wire.
OL,16,FOne group, including a little girl,
OL,17,Fsaid they had come from Honduras and
OL,18,Fhad been stuck on the river bank for
OL,19,Fdays.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G13/14
